I had a similar issue where I was trying to read an existing excel file for template purpose using 

    
        XSSFWorkbook workbook = new XSSFWorkbook(ResourceUtils.getFile(&quot;classpath:legend_wb.xlsx&quot;));

Updating data in memory and sending it as OutputStream for download through REST API but failed to notice that in subsequent downloads whenever sheet had less data, old rows were also coming so basically it as overwriting the cells for whatever data sheet had.

Coming to this question, and following point 3, I wrote following. 

    FileInputStream fis = new FileInputStream(ResourceUtils.getFile(&quot;classpath:legend_wb.xlsx&quot;));
    XSSFWorkbook workbook = new XSSFWorkbook(fis);

 Above code helps to create a copy of existing excel in memory without needing to work on existing excel file directly and also keeps your original excel file intact without any modifications.

